  "text": "For spheres or some other symmetric particle shapes, the mobility and friction matrices are diagonal. Therefore, the mobility center [CITATION_1] coincides with the center of mass, we are in the frame in which the rotational-rotational diffusion tensor is diagonal, and we can directly use the simple analytical expressions derived in [CITATION_2] . For irregular shapes, we first rotate the system of coordinates to the reference frame in which the rotational-rotational diffusion matrix is diagonal. Still, the translational-rotational coupling does not vanish, and therefore, we use more complicated analytical expressions for the cross-correlations from [CITATION_3] . To compare with the experiments, we rotate back the frame of reference to the one shown in Fig. 1 .",
